<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="413" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1412,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="413">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[569,661,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Enoclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incanus">incanus</taxonomicName>
,” Latin for “hoary,” refers to this species’ distinctive elongate white vestiture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
